## 2. What is Asynchronous Apex?

Asynchronous Apex allows Salesforce processes to run in the background without making users wait for completion. It is useful for handling long-running operations, large data volumes, and external integrations.

### Types of Asynchronous Apex

#### Future Methods

Used for simple background processing.

```apex
@future
public static void processData() {
    // Background processing
}
```

#### Queueable Apex

Provides more flexibility and supports complex jobs.

```apex
public class MyQueueableJob implements Queueable {
    public void execute(QueueableContext context) {
        // Job logic
    }
}
```

#### Batch Apex

Processes large numbers of records in manageable batches.

```apex
Database.executeBatch(new MyBatchClass());
```

#### Scheduled Apex

Runs jobs automatically at specified times.

```apex
System.schedule('Daily Job', cronExpression, new MyScheduler());
```

### Advantages

* Better performance.
* Handles large datasets efficiently.
* Improves user experience.
* Supports automation and integrations.

