## 4. Complete System Workflow (End-to-End Explanation)

### Step 1: Requirement Analysis

Business requirements are gathered and documented.

### Step 2: Development

Developers create Apex classes, triggers, Lightning Web Components, and Flows.

### Step 3: Source Control

Code is committed to Git repositories.

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Added new feature"
git push origin main
```

### Step 4: Scratch Org Creation

Developers create temporary environments for development and testing.

```bash
sf org create scratch
```

### Step 5: Deployment to Scratch Org

Metadata is deployed for validation.

```bash
sf project deploy start
```

### Step 6: Testing

Apex test classes are executed.

```bash
sf apex run test
```

### Step 7: Code Review

Team members review code quality, security, and best practices.

### Step 8: CI/CD Pipeline

Automated tools build, test, and validate the application.

### Step 9: Deployment to Production

After successful testing, code is deployed to production.

### Step 10: Monitoring and Maintenance

Applications are monitored and updated when necessary.

### Workflow Diagram

```
Requirements
      ↓
Development
      ↓
Git Repository
      ↓
Scratch Org
      ↓
Testing
      ↓
Code Review
      ↓
CI/CD Pipeline
      ↓
Production Deployment
      ↓
Maintenance
```

