## 6. Reflection: Why Enterprise Software Development Needs Structured Workflows

Enterprise software systems are large, complex, and used by many users. A structured workflow ensures that development activities are organized, predictable, and maintainable.

### Reasons Structured Workflows Are Important

* Improves software quality through testing and reviews.
* Reduces deployment risks.
* Encourages collaboration among team members.
* Enables version control and traceability.
* Supports continuous improvement and maintenance.
* Ensures compliance with organizational standards.
* Makes troubleshooting and debugging easier.

In Salesforce projects, combining Testing, Salesforce DX, Git, and CI/CD creates a reliable development process that helps teams deliver secure, scalable, and high-quality applications efficiently.
